<li id="cite_note-26"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-26">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation web">Greg Neyman (2011). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.answersincreation.org/theistic_evolution.htm">"Theistic Evolution"</a>. Answers in Creation<span class="printonly">. <a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="http://www.answersincreation.org/theistic_evolution.htm">http://www.answersincreation.org/theistic_evolution.htm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved 24 April 2012</span>. "Theistic Evolution is the old earth creationist belief that God used the process of evolution to create life on earth. The modern scientific understanding of biological evolution is considered to be compatible with the Bible."</span></span></li>
